why each library is needed:
	•	pandas, numpy → data wrangling + math.
	•	yfinance → fetch stock prices.
	•	newsapi-python → fetch news headlines.
	•	scikit-learn, xgboost → ML models for prediction.
	•	transformers, torch, sentence-transformers → NLP models like FinBERT.
	•	streamlit → simple dashboard/UI.
	•	matplotlib → visualizations (charts).

market-analyzer/
│── venv/                  # virtual environment (ignored in .gitignore)
│── data/                  # raw and processed data
│   └── __init__.py
│── models/                # ML/NLP models
│   └── __init__.py
│── dashboard/             # Streamlit dashboard files
│   └── __init__.py
│── utils/                 # helper functions
│   └── __init__.py
│── main.py                # entry point (run pipeline)
│── requirements.txt       # list of dependencies
│── README.md              # project overview for GitHub